# Optimizations
def AsymptoticZ0(N_obs, Nb):
    # Ensuring Nb != 0
    Nb += 1e-9
    s = N_obs - Nb
    return np.sqrt(2 * ((s + Nb) * np.log(1 + s/Nb) - s)) if np.any(Nb > 0) else 0

def SimplifiedZ0(N_obs, Nb):
    Zscore = (N_obs - Nb) / np.sqrt(Nb)
    return Zscore

The simplified approximation gives way higher significance than the new approximation. Interestingly, for small positive values of s & b, they're most different trends. At higher positive values, it follows the general trend with significantly different magnitudes of rates. Scenarios where b (qcd_weights) is absolutely massive means that the noise essentially completely drowns out the signal. Then, it's obvious as to why the new approximation, or really any approximation, would fail

from scipy.stats import poisson
# Parameters
higgs_eff, qcd_eff = 0.008463, 5.2e-5

# Single trial function
def run_trial(n_higgs, n_qcd):
    n_higgs_obs = poisson.rvs(mu=n_higgs)
    n_qcd_obs = poisson.rvs(mu=n_qcd)
    total_events = n_higgs_obs + n_qcd_obs
    return AsymptoticZ0(total_events,n_qcd_obs)

def trials(n_higgs, n_qcd):
    signif = [run_trial(n_higgs, n_qcd) for _ in range(999)]
    return np.median(signif)

med_sign = []
for i in range(len(bkgrnd_num)):

    med_sign.append(tmp)

plt.title('Significance vs Higgs & QCD Total w/ Poisson')

# Function to create a table of all features
def valtable(datafile):
    templab = datafile['data']['block0_items']
    column_names = [name.decode('utf-8') for name in templab]
    values = datafile['data']['block0_values']
    df = pd.DataFrame(values,columns=column_names)
    return df

    plt.hist(hlum[var],bins=60,histtype='step',label='High Lumi')

sigr = 100/(100+20000)
bkgr = 20000/(100+20000)
# Weights
qcd_weight = 20000/len(qcd)
higgs_weight = 100/len(higgs)
hlum_weight = (100+20000)/len(hlum)

def plot(bin,var):
    sig = higgs[var]
    bkg = qcd[var]
    count_sig, bin_sig = np.histogram(sig,density=True,bins=bin)
    count_bkg, bin_bkg = np.histogram(bkg,density=True,bins=bin)
    bin_width = bin_bkg[1]-bin_bkg[0]
    exp_sig = np.array([nb for nb in len(hlum) * sigr * bin_width * count_sig])
    exp_bkg = np.array([nb for nb in len(hlum) * bkgr * bin_width * count_bkg])
    exp_tot = exp_sig + exp_bkg

    plt.hist([bin_bkg[:-1],bin_sig[:-1]],bin_bkg,histtype='step',
             stacked=True,fill=False,weights=[exp_bkg,exp_sig])
    counts,bin_edges=np.histogram(hlum[var],bin_bkg)
    bin_center = (bin_edges[:-1]+bin_edges[1:])/2
    plt.errorbar(bin_center,counts,yerr=np.sqrt(counts),fmt='.')
    plt.xlabel(var)
    plt.ylabel('# of Events')
    plt.title(f'High-lumi {var} sig & bkg (pre-cut)')
    plt.show()

                (df['d2'] > 0.6) & (df['d2'] < 2) &
                (df['pt'] > 480) & (df['pt'] < 490) &

hlum_cut = hlum.loc[(hlum['mass'] > 120) & (hlum['mass'] < 130) &
                (hlum['d2'] > 0.6) & (hlum['d2'] < 2) &
                (hlum['pt'] > 480) & (hlum['pt'] < 490) &
                (hlum['t2'] > 0.12) & (hlum['t2'] < 0.4)]

llum_cut = llum.loc[(llum['mass'] > 120) & (llum['mass'] < 130) &
                (llum['d2'] > 0.6) & (llum['d2'] < 2) &
                (llum['pt'] > 480) & (llum['pt'] < 490) &
                (llum['t2'] > 0.12) & (llum['t2'] < 0.4)]

sig_r = len(higgs_cut)/1e5
bkg_r = len(qcd_cut)/1e5

# Cut plot
def cut_plot(bin,var):
    sig = higgs_cut[var]
    bkg = qcd_cut[var]
    count_sig, bin_sig = np.histogram(sig,density=True,bins=bin)
    count_bkg, bin_bkg = np.histogram(bkg,density=True,bins=bin)
    bin_width = bin_bkg[1]-bin_bkg[0]
    exp_sig = np.array([nb for nb in len(hlum) * sig_r * sigr * bin_width * count_sig])
    exp_bkg = np.array([nb for nb in len(hlum) * bkg_r * bkgr * bin_width * count_bkg])
    exp_tot = exp_sig + exp_bkg

    plt.hist([bin_bkg[:-1],bin_sig[:-1]],bin_bkg,histtype='step',
             stacked=True,fill=False,weights=[exp_bkg,exp_sig])
    
    counts,bin_edges=np.histogram(hlum_cut[var],bin_bkg)
    bin_center = (bin_edges[:-1]+bin_edges[1:])/2
    plt.errorbar(bin_center,counts,yerr=np.sqrt(counts)/4,fmt='.')
    plt.xlabel(var)
    plt.ylabel('# of Events')
    plt.title(f'High-lumi {var} sig & bkg (post-cut)')
    plt.show()

loc = (ll_bkg != 0) & (ll_sig_bkg != 0)
print(ll_bkg[loc]/ll_sig_bkg[loc])
